WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.167 --> 00:00:03.000
Previously on X-Men...

2
00:00:03.083 --> 00:00:06.708
I looked for months.
I couldn't find a trace of them.

3
00:00:06.792 --> 00:00:08.583
The X-Men are dead.

4
00:00:08.667 --> 00:00:13.833
Luckily this ain't our first time
at "The X-Men are dead" rodeo.

5
00:00:13.917 --> 00:00:16.125
But it's less a question about where.

6
00:00:17.167 --> 00:00:19.667
and more when.

7
00:00:20.375 --> 00:00:22.875
What is the saying?
"We are not in Kansas"?

8
00:00:25.208 --> 00:00:28.458
Dang asteroid exploded.
now we're here.

9
00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:30.417
Enough!

10
00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:34.917
Perhaps our recently rescued friend
holds the answers to our location.

11
00:00:36.125 --> 00:00:37.708
What is your name?

12
00:00:38.625 --> 00:00:39.750
My name...

13
00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:42.542
is En Sabah Nur.

14
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:50.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

15
00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:59.167
So much for "home sweet home."

16
00:02:00.125 --> 00:02:01.625
Bishop and I had a plan.

17
00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:06.083
Collect you all
and meet here at this exact point in time.

18
00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:08.583
But they're not back.

19
00:02:09.792 --> 00:02:12.125
And the signals on their time bands
are dead.

20
00:02:13.750 --> 00:02:15.458
Then we go after them.

21
00:02:15.542 --> 00:02:18.875
We have no way to pinpoint where they are.

22
00:02:18.958 --> 00:02:20.208
And the longer they're gone.

23
00:02:20.292 --> 00:02:24.583
the more chances there are for
the entire time stream to be rewritten.

24
00:02:25.417 --> 00:02:29.500
Mother Askani sent them to stop the rise
of Apocalypse from ever coming to pass.

25
00:02:30.917 --> 00:02:34.792
If we cannot reach them.
we must hope they succeed.

26
00:02:52.750 --> 00:02:58.458
It comes as a heavy burden
to be the first of your kind.

27
00:02:59.125 --> 00:03:01.125
I may have abilities.

28
00:03:01.208 --> 00:03:04.417
but they do not change the fact
that people like me

29
00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:08.292
are only privileged to dream of survival.

30
00:03:09.125 --> 00:03:14.792
That is a story told by oppressors
who need for you to fear them.

31
00:03:14.875 --> 00:03:21.458
When in truth. it is they who fear you
and what you could become.

32
00:03:21.542 --> 00:03:22.583
And what is that?

33
00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:27.417
With my guidance. a god among insects.

34
00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:30.667
You speak of power to a man born a slave.

35
00:03:31.375 --> 00:03:34.375
A conquest of a cruel pharaoh
from a foreign land.

36
00:03:34.458 --> 00:03:38.000
Yes. but it is only through struggle

37
00:03:38.083 --> 00:03:44.000
that one comes to understand
the true value of power.

38
00:03:56.750 --> 00:03:58.833
Pharaoh. the Sandstormers.

39
00:03:58.917 --> 00:04:00.208
They approach the city.

40
00:04:00.292 --> 00:04:03.583
led by the abomination
they call En Sabah Nur.

41
00:04:03.708 --> 00:04:06.292
En Sabah Nur.

42
00:04:06.375 --> 00:04:09.083
I suppose it was only a matter of time.

43
00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:12.625
-General Logos.
-Yes. sire?

44
00:04:12.708 --> 00:04:15.917
Redirect my forces to the front walls.

45
00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.958
Nur cannot live to challenge me
for the temple or the power I seek.

46
00:04:48.958 --> 00:04:52.083
Halt the work and prepare for battle.

47
00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:56.375
En Sabah Nur rides
with his army of Sandstormers.

48
00:04:56.958 --> 00:05:00.208
They will try to sway you
with their cries of freedom

49
00:05:00.292 --> 00:05:03.583
but remember who holds your chains.

50
00:05:03.667 --> 00:05:09.208
Your one true ruler.
your pharaoh. Rama-Tut.

51
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:13.250
Ya!

52
00:05:33.667 --> 00:05:37.750
You were just a broken child
when I found you in the desert.

53
00:05:37.833 --> 00:05:39.417
Now look at you.

54
00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:42.000
Not just a survivor but a leader.

55
00:05:42.833 --> 00:05:45.875
Soon our desert winds
will sing the song

56
00:05:45.958 --> 00:05:48.042
of our people's freedom.

57
00:05:48.125 --> 00:05:49.792
I promise.

58
00:05:52.042 --> 00:05:54.125
Quite the view.
isn't it. Charles?

59
00:05:54.708 --> 00:05:59.458
We are trapped 5.000 years
before our time.

60
00:05:59.542 --> 00:06:04.208
And you risk our fates on a mutant
who cannot be trusted.

61
00:06:04.292 --> 00:06:07.750
Your students said the same of me
when you left me your school.

62
00:06:08.292 --> 00:06:11.042
The Pharaoh's technology
is clearly from the future.

63
00:06:11.125 --> 00:06:14.167
perhaps even from a time beyond ours.

64
00:06:14.250 --> 00:06:16.083
It could help us return home.

65
00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:18.875
If we trust En Sabah Nur.

66
00:06:18.958 --> 00:06:21.500
His name is Apocalypse.

67
00:06:21.583 --> 00:06:23.833
Bringer of Chaos.

68
00:06:23.917 --> 00:06:26.250
Lord of Destruction.

69
00:06:26.333 --> 00:06:29.500
The X-Men's most diabolical foe.

70
00:06:29.583 --> 00:06:33.625
An immortal madman known
for crushing his enemies.

71
00:06:33.708 --> 00:06:34.958
not capturing them.

72
00:06:35.042 --> 00:06:37.458
Not in this era.

73
00:06:37.542 --> 00:06:39.458
Not today.

74
00:06:39.542 --> 00:06:42.500
Here he is still the first mutant.

75
00:06:42.583 --> 00:06:49.417
Magnus. Nur does not know
who we really are or when we are from.

76
00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.875
And yet he trusts me.

77
00:06:51.958 --> 00:06:55.625
Can you not do the same.
after everything we've been through?

78
00:06:59.625 --> 00:07:02.250
We were born slaves.

79
00:07:02.333 --> 00:07:05.083
Shackled before we could walk.

80
00:07:05.833 --> 00:07:08.292
Beaten before we could fight.

81
00:07:10.167 --> 00:07:13.458
But men like us shall kneel no longer.

82
00:07:14.208 --> 00:07:16.042
We will survive.

83
00:07:16.833 --> 00:07:19.208
For we belong to the future.

84
00:07:21.792 --> 00:07:24.958
And the future belongs to the strong.

85
00:07:25.042 --> 00:07:26.958
Survival of the fittest!

86
00:07:27.042 --> 00:07:31.458
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

87
00:07:31.542 --> 00:07:34.458
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

88
00:07:34.542 --> 00:07:38.083
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

89
00:08:01.125 --> 00:08:02.375
Baal!

90
00:08:16.083 --> 00:08:19.333
Desert rat.

91
00:08:31.917 --> 00:08:35.958
I suppose perseverance
is the virtue of a slave.

92
00:09:45.167 --> 00:09:48.250
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

93
00:09:48.333 --> 00:09:50.292
Come now. Seize his head.

94
00:09:50.375 --> 00:09:53.958
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

95
00:09:54.042 --> 00:09:57.125
Survival of the fittest!
Survival of the fittest!

96
00:09:57.208 --> 00:10:00.208
Survival of the fittest...

97
00:10:10.708 --> 00:10:12.500
We take him alive.

98
00:10:13.375 --> 00:10:15.875
Send the team
to recover the fallen Androids.

99
00:10:15.958 --> 00:10:18.000
Then leave Nur to me.

100
00:10:18.083 --> 00:10:22.000
I promise I will see our X-Men
safely home. old friend.

101
00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:27.167
Delivery for the good Dr. McCoy.

102
00:10:27.250 --> 00:10:28.958
Fresh from En Sabah Nur's battle.

103
00:10:29.833 --> 00:10:31.917
Had everything
but the kitchen sink

104
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:34.250
thrown at us the past few months.

105
00:10:34.333 --> 00:10:36.708
What are the odds
this bucket of spare junk

106
00:10:36.792 --> 00:10:38.625
will actually get us home?

107
00:10:38.708 --> 00:10:40.042
Were you seen?

108
00:10:40.125 --> 00:10:42.833
Oh. Professor. ye of little faith.

109
00:10:42.917 --> 00:10:44.542
Not a soul saw me.

110
00:10:44.625 --> 00:10:47.917
Although in an ancient Egypt
of murderous robots.

111
00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.458
I would imagine a demon lurking among them
would hardly come as a surprise.

112
00:10:52.542 --> 00:10:55.875
Beast. I punched in
the last of your coordinates.

113
00:10:55.958 --> 00:10:57.625
She's ready to go.

114
00:10:57.708 --> 00:11:01.292
Pray this time
the machine works to take us home.

115
00:11:19.917 --> 00:11:22.167
Oh!

116
00:11:26.292 --> 00:11:28.292
Ah!

117
00:11:28.375 --> 00:11:30.125
Blast these machines!

118
00:11:30.833 --> 00:11:34.042
May as well be a cat pawing
at a ball of yarn.

119
00:11:34.125 --> 00:11:36.833
Hank. self-flagellation helps no one.

120
00:11:36.917 --> 00:11:38.208
You have done your best.

121
00:11:38.833 --> 00:11:40.875
I just don't have enough power.

122
00:11:40.958 --> 00:11:44.125
How can the Pharaoh's technology
be so frightfully advanced

123
00:11:44.208 --> 00:11:45.792
yet also incredibly primeval?

124
00:11:45.875 --> 00:11:50.167
Perhaps mere mortals were not meant
to tame forces such as time.

125
00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:54.750
Then I fear praying to the gods
may soon be our only option.

126
00:11:55.500 --> 00:11:59.042
For the power to create
a stable temporal displacement field

127
00:11:59.125 --> 00:12:01.958
can only be described as cosmic.

128
00:12:02.542 --> 00:12:06.417
Magneto believes General Logos
may be able to provide the insight we need

129
00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:08.458
to adapt the Pharaoh's technology.

130
00:12:08.542 --> 00:12:12.083
Assuming En Sabah Nur
doesn't kill him first.

131
00:12:12.167 --> 00:12:16.042
Our fates now rest on an alliance
between our oldest adversary.

132
00:12:16.125 --> 00:12:19.375
and our most merciless one.

133
00:12:19.458 --> 00:12:21.042
Talk about faith. no?

134
00:12:36.750 --> 00:12:40.833
Before you came into my life.
these men only saw me as a monster.

135
00:12:41.417 --> 00:12:44.125
But with your counsel.
they no longer fear me.

136
00:12:44.208 --> 00:12:45.833
They follow me.

137
00:12:45.917 --> 00:12:47.417
Though I must confess.

138
00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:51.000
every part of me still
longs to crush this insect.

139
00:12:51.625 --> 00:12:54.542
Only a coward feels mighty
when stepping on ants.

140
00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:58.917
Baal would disagree vehemently.

141
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.417
With the sentiment or with me?

142
00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.542
Let us just say
he has never been one

143
00:13:03.625 --> 00:13:06.000
to offer outsiders his trust.

144
00:13:06.583 --> 00:13:08.750
Sparing Logos was the right decision.

145
00:13:08.833 --> 00:13:13.250
As mutants.
we must resist our darkest impulses

146
00:13:13.333 --> 00:13:15.667
if we're ever to save humanity
from itself.

147
00:13:19.208 --> 00:13:21.083
Apologies.

148
00:13:21.167 --> 00:13:24.125
Your plan to extract vital intelligence
from the Pharaoh's general

149
00:13:24.208 --> 00:13:26.667
is to have Apocalypse ask him nicely?

150
00:13:26.750 --> 00:13:30.125
I thought "nicely" was
how the X-Men preferred to do things.

151
00:13:30.208 --> 00:13:32.917
Professor. we're wasting time.

152
00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.083
Just pull the information
out of his dang head.

153
00:13:36.167 --> 00:13:37.958
Using my powers on him

154
00:13:38.042 --> 00:13:41.500
increases the risk of us
altering the past here.

155
00:13:42.458 --> 00:13:44.958
Perhaps we are already fate's puppets.

156
00:13:45.625 --> 00:13:50.125
Is it not more than a coincidence
that the Professor's extraordinary gifts

157
00:13:50.208 --> 00:13:52.833
are the perfect solution
to our predicament?

158
00:13:52.917 --> 00:13:56.542
In either case. removing us from this era
as quickly as possible

159
00:13:56.625 --> 00:13:58.250
is in everyone's best interest.

160
00:13:58.917 --> 00:14:01.958
I fear to consider
what disturbances we could unleash

161
00:14:02.042 --> 00:14:03.792
if someone were to learn the truth.

162
00:14:05.292 --> 00:14:07.458
Peaceful greetings. fellow mutants.

163
00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:14.917
Greetings and congratulations. Nur.

164
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:19.125
You honor me. Charles. Today's victory
belongs to all around this table.

165
00:14:21.125 --> 00:14:25.667
So many nights as a boy.
an outcast amongst slaves.

166
00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:29.792
Glaring up at the stars.
cursing. praying. Why?

167
00:14:30.542 --> 00:14:32.667
In whose image was I made?

168
00:14:32.750 --> 00:14:36.875
Never in a million moons dared I dream
of meeting others like me.

169
00:14:38.583 --> 00:14:40.875
Dreams help us survive.

170
00:14:41.708 --> 00:14:43.708
Perhaps even more than blades and arrows.

171
00:14:43.792 --> 00:14:46.958
I have never seen an enemy
quake before a dream.

172
00:14:47.042 --> 00:14:51.542
Nor seen a dream lay siege to a fortress
such as the Pharaoh's capital.

173
00:14:51.625 --> 00:14:55.167
-Baal. be gentle.
-Gentle?

174
00:14:56.583 --> 00:14:59.292
The men whisper. Soul Son.

175
00:14:59.375 --> 00:15:02.417
We could have torn through every wall
in that city today

176
00:15:02.500 --> 00:15:04.333
but you stopped after one.

177
00:15:05.125 --> 00:15:07.958
Out of fear of facing the Pharaoh.

178
00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:13.542
You do not yet understand his army
enough to vanquish it.

179
00:15:13.625 --> 00:15:17.583
How many of these same men would die
at the hands of his machines?

180
00:15:18.083 --> 00:15:20.458
How many are fit to survive?

181
00:15:20.542 --> 00:15:22.500
Silence. both of you!

182
00:15:22.583 --> 00:15:24.792
We all share in Egypt's future.

183
00:15:24.875 --> 00:15:27.000
Your new friends.

184
00:15:27.750 --> 00:15:31.458
Their ambitions for you are so very small.

185
00:15:31.542 --> 00:15:35.458
When I freed you from the camp.
I promised you the world.

186
00:15:36.083 --> 00:15:38.208
Magnus says I have a destiny.

187
00:15:38.958 --> 00:15:41.542
I can do more than just conquer the world.

188
00:15:42.333 --> 00:15:44.042
I can save it.

189
00:15:44.125 --> 00:15:48.458
You have until tomorrow's moon
to get the answers you seek.

190
00:15:48.542 --> 00:15:50.792
Then I take the head of Logos.

191
00:15:51.667 --> 00:15:54.833
your destiny or not.

192
00:15:56.250 --> 00:16:00.875
You told Nur we see a destiny for him?

193
00:16:03.708 --> 00:16:06.333
I can explain. Charles.

194
00:16:07.208 --> 00:16:11.583
This is what your interest
has been in him all along.

195
00:16:11.667 --> 00:16:14.417
Not to help us find a way home

196
00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:19.667
but to coerce him into embracing my dream
of mutant-human harmony.

197
00:16:20.292 --> 00:16:23.708
What if a mutant with Apocalypse's power
had championed your dream

198
00:16:23.792 --> 00:16:26.125
5.000 years before you did?

199
00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:28.875
Not merely the first mutant.

200
00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:31.542
The first X-Man.

201
00:16:31.625 --> 00:16:35.167
A chance to rewrite all of history
in our favor.

202
00:16:35.875 --> 00:16:41.167
The risks of altering time on that scale
without humanity's consent...

203
00:16:41.250 --> 00:16:45.000
Please. Mankind has long authored history.

204
00:16:45.083 --> 00:16:46.083
The result?

205
00:16:46.750 --> 00:16:49.375
Countless volumes of trite barbarism.

206
00:16:49.458 --> 00:16:52.750
Every new chapter scrolled in blood.

207
00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:56.875
Each generation plagiarizing the prior.

208
00:16:56.958 --> 00:16:59.292
From these Sandstormers to the cowards

209
00:16:59.375 --> 00:17:01.833
who sponsored Bastion's
smiting of Genosha.

210
00:17:04.667 --> 00:17:07.458
Genosha
was not your fault. Magnus.

211
00:17:08.875 --> 00:17:11.542
No. it was ours.

212
00:17:12.125 --> 00:17:14.083
I brought mutants there.

213
00:17:14.958 --> 00:17:16.875
Helped make it a nation.

214
00:17:18.125 --> 00:17:19.750
For you.

215
00:17:19.833 --> 00:17:22.542
My intention was to inspire.

216
00:17:22.625 --> 00:17:26.625
Yes. inspire me to be like you.

217
00:17:26.708 --> 00:17:29.375
But I am not. No one is.

218
00:17:30.208 --> 00:17:32.042
Help me. Charles.

219
00:17:32.125 --> 00:17:36.500
and your X-Men will return to a world
far beyond our wildest dreams.

220
00:17:36.583 --> 00:17:41.208
One where your dream
has finally come true.

221
00:17:42.792 --> 00:17:45.667
For our sake and the world's.

222
00:17:46.417 --> 00:17:48.458
I do hope it's possible

223
00:17:49.292 --> 00:17:52.167
for Nur's rage to be contained.

224
00:17:54.167 --> 00:17:57.667
I say again. tell us the secrets
of the Pharaoh's technology

225
00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:59.958
and your life will be spared.

226
00:18:02.292 --> 00:18:04.042
Oh. you have grown.

227
00:18:04.125 --> 00:18:08.375
You're not the wailing gray pup
with crooked lips any more.

228
00:18:08.458 --> 00:18:11.333
left by his mother to bake in the sand.

229
00:18:12.208 --> 00:18:13.875
You truly don't remember?

230
00:18:13.958 --> 00:18:18.417
You were so young
and the years so painful.

231
00:18:18.500 --> 00:18:20.542
You will answer me!

232
00:18:20.625 --> 00:18:24.292
Took a moment. but I'd never forget
the disfigured face

233
00:18:24.375 --> 00:18:26.750
of Rama-Tut's favorite slave.

234
00:18:27.958 --> 00:18:29.000
You?

235
00:18:29.542 --> 00:18:30.542
You are...

236
00:18:30.625 --> 00:18:34.917
Your first master who put you
in your pharaoh's chains.

237
00:18:40.917 --> 00:18:42.917
You are not your past. En Sabah Nur.

238
00:18:43.708 --> 00:18:45.458
You are our future.

239
00:18:46.583 --> 00:18:49.750
You want me to let this dog live?

240
00:18:51.250 --> 00:18:52.458
I do.

241
00:18:55.500 --> 00:18:58.708
I leave him to you. then.

242
00:19:00.292 --> 00:19:03.792
You laugh at our mercy?

243
00:19:03.875 --> 00:19:08.208
You and your desert vermin can continue
your rebellion all you want.

244
00:19:08.708 --> 00:19:11.417
The Pharaoh is on the precipice
of a discovery

245
00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:14.292
that will make his current army
look like playthings.

246
00:19:14.375 --> 00:19:15.458
What?

247
00:19:15.542 --> 00:19:19.958
A lost temple of divine beings
from the stars.

248
00:19:20.042 --> 00:19:25.458
Blessed with the means to turn
our mortal Pharaoh into a god himself.

249
00:19:25.542 --> 00:19:27.000
Magnus.

250
00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:29.875
This could be
the power we need to get home.

251
00:19:29.958 --> 00:19:32.875
You will tell us about this temple.

252
00:19:32.958 --> 00:19:37.542
I do not cower before
the Sandstormers' abomination.

253
00:19:37.625 --> 00:19:40.583
You expect me to fear you?

254
00:19:41.042 --> 00:19:43.250
You leave me no choice.

255
00:19:43.917 --> 00:19:45.875
Do not resist me.

256
00:19:45.958 --> 00:19:49.333
I will know it all in time.

257
00:19:54.792 --> 00:19:56.958
Surrender your mind to me.

258
00:19:58.000 --> 00:20:02.625
Show me the location
of this temple of the star gods.

259
00:20:11.833 --> 00:20:14.375
Ah! Ah!

260
00:20:25.583 --> 00:20:32.042
I am the tide that carries
all to the Rocks of the Eternal Shore.

261
00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:37.542
Crash against them and be broken.

262
00:20:41.875 --> 00:20:48.375
Everything everywhere
finds their way here. the end.

263
00:20:48.458 --> 00:20:50.708
I can sense you.

264
00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:53.083
Whoever you are. reveal yourself.

265
00:20:53.667 --> 00:20:56.917
In time. all will see.

266
00:20:57.000 --> 00:21:00.750
He is where the end begins.

267
00:21:00.833 --> 00:21:02.708
Begins.

268
00:21:07.792 --> 00:21:09.875
It's me. Charles. it's me.

269
00:21:13.292 --> 00:21:15.625
I searched Logos's mind.

270
00:21:15.708 --> 00:21:20.542
And he only knew but pieces
of the lost temple's location.

271
00:21:21.708 --> 00:21:24.917
And I am not sure
we should wish to know it either.

272
00:21:26.042 --> 00:21:27.708
A presence called me from it.

273
00:21:28.458 --> 00:21:33.167
Grand. offensive.
Unlike any I've encountered.

274
00:21:33.958 --> 00:21:36.500
It will not tolerate us
finding this place.

275
00:21:37.375 --> 00:21:39.417
Do not worry. old friend.

276
00:21:40.042 --> 00:21:44.667
Whatever forces await.
we shall face them together.

277
00:21:49.333 --> 00:21:51.500
Your treasure hunt is over.

278
00:21:52.167 --> 00:21:53.375
As is your treachery.

279
00:21:55.375 --> 00:21:57.292
Magnus. what is the meaning of this?

280
00:21:57.958 --> 00:22:00.292
Lift the wool from your eyes. Nur.

281
00:22:00.375 --> 00:22:02.833
This so-called prophet has lied to you.

282
00:22:02.917 --> 00:22:05.542
He hides their true intent.

283
00:22:05.625 --> 00:22:09.125
They hoard the very machines
we seek to destroy.

284
00:22:09.208 --> 00:22:11.542
You are using them to build something.

285
00:22:11.625 --> 00:22:13.417
A weapon for yourself?

286
00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:16.917
Nur. give me a chance to explain.

287
00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.708
You have deceived me.

288
00:22:18.792 --> 00:22:19.958
Your own.

289
00:22:20.958 --> 00:22:22.458
I'm sorry. Nur.

290
00:22:22.542 --> 00:22:25.708
Lies are weapons of the weak.

291
00:22:25.792 --> 00:22:27.333
Nur. please. no!

292
00:22:32.125 --> 00:22:34.708
He was not fit to survive.

293
00:22:36.708 --> 00:22:38.375
Destroy them!

294
00:22:50.500 --> 00:22:52.083
It seems we are not alone.

295
00:22:59.625 --> 00:23:02.042
-Ugh!
-Baal. no!

296
00:23:12.083 --> 00:23:14.417
En Sabah Nur.

297
00:23:14.500 --> 00:23:16.708
You thought you could hide.

298
00:23:16.792 --> 00:23:18.750
But I found you.

299
00:23:20.208 --> 00:23:21.833
Time to deplete the reserves.

300
00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:29.542
Well. I'll be! Bishop!

301
00:23:29.625 --> 00:23:30.792
Gratitude later.

302
00:23:30.875 --> 00:23:33.667
We got to get you back home now
before he comes to.

303
00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:37.042
What of the others?
Have they returned to our time?

304
00:23:37.125 --> 00:23:38.458
Long story.

305
00:23:38.542 --> 00:23:39.917
But Forge is on top of it.

306
00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:43.167
Let us see
who is more fit to survive.

307
00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:46.875
The slave or the conqueror?

308
00:23:58.333 --> 00:24:02.500
Magnus. I fear that the time
to redeem Nur has passed.

309
00:24:02.583 --> 00:24:04.167
Save it for the history books.

310
00:24:04.250 --> 00:24:06.125
Time to get the hell out of this place.

311
00:24:06.208 --> 00:24:07.958
We need you back in the 1990s.

312
00:24:13.292 --> 00:24:15.958
Our fight is not done!

312
00:24:16.305 --> 00:25:16.896
Do you want subtitles for any video?
